<paragraph blockId="19.[113,764,282,1949]" lastBlockId="19.[801,1452,283,372]" pageId="19" pageNumber="218">
Sporophyte. 
<emphasis box="[285,327,1539,1562]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="218">Seta</emphasis>
up to 3.5 mm long, straight, vaginula 0.8 mm long, cylindrical. 
<emphasis box="[353,434,1571,1595]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="218">Capsule</emphasis>
emergent, erect, obloid, occasionally slightly asymmetric, smooth, exothecial cells mostly elongated, rarely pentagonal, walls thin or thick, depending on orientation and focusing, curvilinear, stomata none, at orifice several rows of transversely rectangular cells, the two upper rows suggesting a persistent annulus. 
<taxonomicName box="[438,524,1732,1756]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Calyptra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="218" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[438,524,1732,1756]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="218">Calyptra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cucullate, covering part of capsule. 
<emphasis box="[225,331,1764,1788]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="218">Operculum</emphasis>
conical, rostrate or rostellate, beak straight or oblique, blunt, margin uneven, some rows of small, rounded marginal cells, in conical part larger oval or rounded cells. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="218">Peristome</emphasis>
teeth erect when dry, lanceolate, irregularly perforated or slit to two unequal branches, lower dorsal part smooth, subsequent plates sparsely covered with fine papillae, upper dorsal and ventral sides densely covered with fine papillae, trabeculae thin, in lower part close together, in upper part distant, slightly protruding. 
<emphasis box="[926,987,348,371]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="218">Spores</emphasis>
10-12 µm, smooth.
</paragraph>
